  "text": "the association between HCV RNA and vitamin D serum concentration we used the cut-off value of 400 000 IU/ml [CITATION_1] . In patients with baseline HCV RNA < 400 000 IU/ml (n = 25; 46%) and ≥ 10 000 copies/ml (n = 29; 54%), mean vitamin D concentrations were 20.1 ng/ml and 17.9 ng/ml, respectively. The difference between groups was not statistically significant (p = 0.44).",
